[2;36m                    [0m         [39m==[0m[1;36m18[0m[39m==ABORTING[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msubprocess command returned a non-zero exit status: [0m[1;36m1[0m                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mINFO:__main__:Running: docker run --privileged --shm-[0m[33msize[0m[39m=[0m[35m2g[0m[39m --platform linux/amd64[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m--rm -i -e [0m[33mHELPER[0m[39m=[0m[3;92mTrue[0m[39m -e [0m[33mARCHITECTURE[0m[39m=[0m[35mx86_64[0m[39m -v [0m                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [35m/home/qqor/crete/packages/python_oss_fuzz/.oss_fuzz/build/out/[0m[95mlcms[0m[39m:[0m[35m/[0m[95mout[0m[39m -v [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [35m/tmp/[0m[95mtmp7f_uzkdz[0m[39m:[0m[35m/[0m[95mtestcase[0m[39m -t ghcr.io/aixcc-finals/base-runner:v1.[0m[1;36m3.0[0m[39m reproduce [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcms_virtual_profile_fuzzer -[0m[33mruns[0m[39m=[0m[1;36m100[0m[39m.[0m                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m===Evaluation [0m[33mReport[0m[39m===[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m# Evaluation Report[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Summary[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mA stack-buffer-overflow vulnerability has been detected in the lcms library during [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfuzzing of the `cms_virtual_profile_fuzzer`. The issue manifests as a [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m-byte read [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mbeyond the bounds of a stack-allocated variable in the `UnrollChunkyBytes` [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfunction, triggered through the color transformation and device link creation code [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mpath. AddressSanitizer reports a SCARINESS score of [0m[1;36m27[0m[39m for this [0m                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m-byte-read-stack-buffer-overflow.[0m                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Description[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Vulnerability Type[0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe issue is a **stack-buffer-overflow** vulnerability, specifically a read [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39moperation that extends [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m byte beyond the allocated buffer boundary. [0m                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mAddressSanitizer has classified this as a [0m[32m"1-byte-read-stack-buffer-overflow"[0m[39m with [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39ma moderate severity score.[0m                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Issue Details[0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe vulnerability occurs during the execution of color transformation operations in[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthe lcms library. The stack trace reveals the following call sequence:[0m              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. The fuzzer entry point `LLVMFuzzerTestOneInput` calls `cmsTransform2DeviceLink` [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. `cmsTransform2DeviceLink` invokes `CreateNamedColorDevicelink`[0m                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. This leads to `cmsDoTransform` being called[0m                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. The transform operation triggers `CachedXFORM`[0m                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m5[0m[39m. Finally, `UnrollChunkyBytes` attempts to read beyond buffer boundaries at [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`[0m[35m/src/lcms/src/[0m[95mcmspack.c[0m[39m:[0m[1;92m130:13[0m[39m`[0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe memory access violation occurs at address `[0m[1;36m0x7f0eea539d24[0m[39m`, which [0m              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mAddressSanitizer identifies as offset [0m[1;36m36[0m[39m within a stack frame in the [0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`cmsTransform2DeviceLink` function. The problematic variable is identified as [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`[0m[32m'i.i'[0m[39m` at line [0m[1;36m1071[0m[39m, which is allocated only [0m[1;36m4[0m[39m bytes [0m[1;39m([0m[39mfrom offset [0m[1;36m32[0m[39m to [0m[1;36m36[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, and [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthe read operation attempts to access exactly at offset [0m[1;36m36[0m[39m, which is one byte [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mbeyond the allocated space.[0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Stack Frame Analysis[0m                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe `cmsTransform2DeviceLink` function's stack frame contains [0m[1;36m5[0m[39m objects:[0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- `[0m[1;39m[[0m[1;36m32[0m[39m, [0m[1;36m36[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` - `[0m[32m'i.i'[0m[39m` variable [0m[1;39m([0m[1;36m4[0m[39m bytes[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m - **This is where the overflow occurs**[0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- `[0m[1;39m[[0m[1;36m48[0m[39m, [0m[1;36m52[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` - `[0m[32m'dwFlags.addr'[0m[39m` [0m[1;39m([0m[1;36m4[0m[39m bytes[0m[1;39m)[0m                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- `[0m[1;39m[[0m[1;36m64[0m[39m, [0m[1;36m68[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` - `[0m[32m'FrmIn'[0m[39m` variable [0m[1;39m([0m[1;36m4[0m[39m bytes[0m[1;39m)[0m                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- `[0m[1;39m[[0m[1;36m80[0m[39m, [0m[1;36m84[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` - `[0m[32m'FrmOut'[0m[39m` variable [0m[1;39m([0m[1;36m4[0m[39m bytes[0m[1;39m)[0m                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- `[0m[1;39m[[0m[1;36m96[0m[39m, [0m[1;36m104[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` - `[0m[32m'LUT'[0m[39m` variable [0m[1;39m([0m[1;36m8[0m[39m bytes[0m[1;39m)[0m                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe shadow byte analysis shows that the memory at offset [0m[1;36m36[0m[39m is marked as `[0m[1;39m[[0m[1;36m04[0m[1;39m][0m[39m`, [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mindicating it is partially addressable [0m[1;39m([0m[1;36m4[0m[39m bytes accessible[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, but the read operation[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mattempts to access beyond this boundary.[0m                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Areas for Investigation[0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mTo gain a holistic understanding of this vulnerability, the following components [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mshould be investigated:[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. **`[0m[35m/src/lcms/src/[0m[95mcmspack.c[0m[39m:[0m[1;36m130[0m[39m`** - The immediate location of the buffer [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39moverflow in the `UnrollChunkyBytes` function, where the actual out-of-bounds read [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39moccurs.[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. **`[0m[35m/src/lcms/src/[0m[95mcmsxform.c[0m[39m:[0m[1;36m537[0m[39m`** - The `CachedXFORM` function that calls [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`UnrollChunkyBytes`, to understand the context and parameters being passed.[0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. **`[0m[35m/src/lcms/src/[0m[95mcmsxform.c[0m[39m:[0m[1;36m206[0m[39m`** - The `cmsDoTransform` function that [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39minitiates the transformation process.[0m                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. **`[0m[35m/src/lcms/src/[0m[95mcmsvirt.c[0m[39m:[0m[1;36m1103[0m[39m`** - The `CreateNamedColorDevicelink` function [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthat sets up the named color device link.[0m                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m5[0m[39m. **`[0m[35m/src/lcms/src/[0m[95mcmsvirt.c[0m[39m:[0m[1;36m1185[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m1210[0m[39m`** - The `cmsTransform2DeviceLink` [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfunction, particularly around line [0m[1;36m1071[0m[39m where the `[0m[32m'i.i'[0m[39m` variable is defined, and [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mlines [0m[1;36m1187[0m[39m where `FrmIn` and `FrmOut` are defined, to understand how the buffer [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msize is determined and how it relates to the subsequent operations.[0m                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m6[0m[39m. **Buffer size calculations** - The relationship between the allocated buffer [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msize [0m[1;39m([0m[1;36m4[0m[39m bytes for `[0m[32m'i.i'[0m[39m`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m and the actual data being processed needs examination to[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mdetermine if this is an off-by-one error or incorrect size calculation.[0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m7[0m[39m. **Input validation** - The fuzzer input that triggers this condition should be [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39manalyzed to understand what specific characteristics of the test case lead to this [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39moverflow condition.[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m135[0m[39m:            v = [0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m([0m[39mcmsUInt32Number[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m([0m[39mcmsUInt32Number[0m[1;39m)[0m[39mv << [0m[1;36m16[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[35m/[0m[39m alpha_factor[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m136[0m[39m:            if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mv > [0m[1;36m0xffff[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m v = [0m[1;36m0xffff[0m[39m;[0m                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m137[0m[39m:        [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m138[0m[39m:[0m                                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m139[0m[39m:        wIn[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mindex[0m[1;39m][0m[39m = [0m[1;39m([0m[39mcmsUInt16Number[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m v;[0m                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m140[0m[39m:        accum++;[0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m141[0m[39m:    [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m142[0m[39m:[0m                                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m143[0m[39m:    if [0m[1;39m([0m[39m!ExtraFirst[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m144[0m[39m:        accum += Extra;[0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m145[0m[39m:    [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m146[0m[39m:[0m                                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m147[0m[39m:    if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mExtra == [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m && SwapFirst[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m148[0m[39m:        cmsUInt16Number tmp = wIn[0m[1;39m[[0m[1;36m0[0m[1;39m][0m[39m;[0m                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m149[0m[39m:[0m                                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m150[0m[39m:        [0m[1;35mmemmove[0m[1;39m([0m[39m&wIn[0m[1;39m[[0m[1;36m0[0m[1;39m][0m[39m, &wIn[0m[1;39m[[0m[1;36m1[0m[1;39m][0m[39m, [0m[1;39m([0m[39mnChan-[0m[1;36m1[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m * [0m[1;35msizeof[0m[1;39m([0m[39mcmsUInt16Number[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m151[0m[39m:        wIn[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mnChan-[0m[1;36m1[0m[1;39m][0m[39m = tmp;[0m                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m152[0m[39m:    [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m153[0m[39m:[0m                                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m154[0m[39m:    return accum;[0m                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m155[0m[39m:[0m                                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m156[0m[39m:    [0m[1;35mcmsUNUSED_PARAMETER[0m[1;39m([0m[39minfo[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m157[0m[39m:    [0m[1;35mcmsUNUSED_PARAMETER[0m[1;39m([0m[39mStride[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m158[0m[39m:[0m                                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m159[0m[39m:[0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode[0m[39m>[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<code>[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msrc/cmsxform.[0m[1;92mc:1441[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m1470[0m                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;92m1441:c[0m[39mmsBool CMSEXPORT [0m[1;35mcmsChangeBuffersFormat[0m[1;39m([0m[39mcmsHTRANSFORM hTransform,[0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1442[0m[39m:                                         cmsUInt32Number InputFormat,[0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1443[0m[39m:                                         cmsUInt32Number OutputFormat[0m[1;39m)[0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1444[0m[39m:[0m[1;39m{[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1445[0m[39m:    _cmsTRANSFORM* xform = [0m[1;39m([0m[39m_cmsTRANSFORM*[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m hTransform;[0m                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1446[0m[39m:    cmsFormatter16 FromInput, ToOutput;[0m                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1447[0m[39m:[0m                                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1448[0m[39m:[0m                                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1449[0m[39m:    [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m We only can afford to change formatters if previous transform is at [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mleast [0m[1;36m16[0m[39m bits[0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1450[0m[39m:    if [0m[1;39m([0m[39m![0m[1;39m([0m[39mxform ->dwOriginalFlags & cmsFLAGS_CAN_CHANGE_FORMATTER[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1451[0m[39m:[0m                                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1452[0m[39m:        [0m[1;35mcmsSignalError[0m[1;39m([0m[39mxform ->ContextID, cmsERROR_NOT_SUITABLE, [0m              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [32m"cmsChangeBuffersFormat works only on transforms created originally with at least [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [32m16 bits of precision"[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1453[0m[39m:        return FALSE;[0m                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1454[0m[39m:    [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1455[0m[39m:[0m                                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1456[0m[39m:    FromInput = [0m[1;35m_cmsGetFormatter[0m[1;39m([0m[39mxform->ContextID, InputFormat,  [0m              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcmsFormatterInput, CMS_PACK_FLAGS_16BITS[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.Fmt16;[0m                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1457[0m[39m:    ToOutput  = [0m[1;35m_cmsGetFormatter[0m[1;39m([0m[39mxform->ContextID, OutputFormat, [0m              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcmsFormatterOutput, CMS_PACK_FLAGS_16BITS[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.Fmt16;[0m                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1458[0m[39m:[0m                                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1459[0m[39m:    if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mFromInput == NULL || ToOutput == NULL[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1460[0m[39m:[0m                                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1461[0m[39m:        [0m[1;35mcmsSignalError[0m[1;39m([0m[39mxform -> ContextID, cmsERROR_UNKNOWN_EXTENSION, [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [32m"Unsupported raster format"[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1462[0m[39m:        return FALSE;[0m                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1463[0m[39m:    [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1464[0m[39m:[0m                                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1465[0m[39m:    xform ->InputFormat  = InputFormat;[0m                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1466[0m[39m:    xform ->OutputFormat = OutputFormat;[0m                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1467[0m[39m:    xform ->FromInput    = FromInput;[0m                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1468[0m[39m:    xform ->ToOutput     = ToOutput;[0m                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1469[0m[39m:    return TRUE;[0m                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1470[0m[39m:[0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode[0m[39m>[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<code>[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msrc/cmspack.[0m[1;92mc:3617[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m3620[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3617[0m[39m:    [0m[1;39m{[0m[39m [0m[1;35mBYTES_SH[0m[1;39m([0m[1;36m1[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m,    ANYFLAVOR|ANYSWAPFIRST|ANYSWAP|ANYPREMUL|[0m                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3618[0m[39m:                                           ANYEXTRA|ANYCHANNELS|ANYSPACE, [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mUnrollChunkyBytes[0m[1;39m}[0m[39m,[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3619[0m[39m:    [0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3620[0m[39m:    [0m[1;39m{[0m[39m [0m[1;35mCHANNELS_SH[0m[1;39m([0m[1;36m1[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m|[0m[1;35mBYTES_SH[0m[1;39m([0m[1;36m2[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m,                              ANYSPACE,  [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mUnroll1Word[0m[1;39m}[0m[39m,[0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode[0m[39m>[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode_snippets[0m[39m>[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Fix Strategy[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<fix_strategy>[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Analysis of the Stack-Buffer-Overflow[0m                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mBased on the evaluation report and code analysis, I can identify the root cause and[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mappropriate fix strategy:[0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Root Cause[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe vulnerability occurs in `CreateNamedColorDevicelink` [0m[1;39m([0m[39msrc/cmsvirt.[0m[1;92mc:1103[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mwhere:[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. A [0m[1;36m4[0m[39m-byte stack variable `i` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mcmsUInt32Number[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m is passed by address to [0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`cmsDoTransform`[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. The InputFormat is set to `TYPE_NAMED_COLOR_INDEX` which specifies [0m              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`[0m[1;35mCHANNELS_SH[0m[1;39m([0m[1;36m1[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m|[0m[1;35mBYTES_SH[0m[1;39m([0m[1;36m2[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` = [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m channel, [0m[1;36m2[0m[39m bytes per sample[0m                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. The formatter `UnrollChunkyBytes` is called [0m[1;39m([0m[39mfor [0m[1;35mBYTES_SH[0m[1;39m([0m[1;36m1[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m formats[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, which [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mreads byte-by-byte from the input[0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. The formatter attempts to read beyond the [0m[1;36m4[0m[39m-byte boundary of variable `i`, [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcausing the overflow at offset [0m[1;36m36[0m[39m [0m[1;39m([0m[39m= [0m[1;36m32[0m[39m + [0m[1;36m4[0m[1;39m)[0m                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe critical issue: While `TYPE_NAMED_COLOR_INDEX` specifies [0m[1;36m2[0m[39m bytes per sample, [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthe actual formatter being used is `UnrollChunkyBytes` which treats data as [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m byte [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mper sample. This mismatch, combined with potential Extra channel flags or other [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mformat flags being set, causes the formatter to read more bytes than available.[0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Analysis of Buffer Access Pattern[0m                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mIn `UnrollChunkyBytes` [0m[1;39m([0m[39msrc/cmspack.[0m[1;92mc:95[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m159[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m:[0m                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Line [0m[1;36m101[0m[39m: `nChan = [0m[1;35mT_CHANNELS[0m[1;39m([0m[39minfo->InputFormat[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` extracts number of channels [0m[1;39m([0m[1;36m1[0m[39m [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfor TYPE_NAMED_COLOR_INDEX[0m[1;39m)[0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Line [0m[1;36m105[0m[39m: `Extra = [0m[1;35mT_EXTRA[0m[1;39m([0m[39minfo->InputFormat[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` extracts extra channels[0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Line [0m[1;36m123[0m[39m: If `!ExtraFirst && Premul && Extra`, reads at `accum[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mnChan[0m[1;39m][0m[39m` position[0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Lines [0m[1;36m126[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m141[0m[39m: Main loop reads `nChan` bytes[0m                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Line [0m[1;36m144[0m[39m: Advances by `Extra` bytes if `!ExtraFirst`[0m                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mFor TYPE_NAMED_COLOR_INDEX with potential format flags, the total bytes accessed [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcould exceed [0m[1;36m4[0m[39m bytes.[0m                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Fix Strategy[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**Primary Fix: Use a properly sized temporary buffer in [0m                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mCreateNamedColorDevicelink**[0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mModify `src/cmsvirt.c` in the `CreateNamedColorDevicelink` function around lines [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1101[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m1104[0m[39m:[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. **Replace the direct use of `&i` with a properly sized buffer**:[0m                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Instead of passing `&i` [0m[1;39m([0m[1;36m4[0m[39m-byte integer pointer[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m directly to `cmsDoTransform`[0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Create a temporary buffer sized according to the InputFormat requirements[0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - For `TYPE_NAMED_COLOR_INDEX`, allocate a [0m[1;36m2[0m[39m-byte buffer [0m[1;39m([0m[39msince [0m[1;35mBYTES_SH[0m[1;39m([0m[1;36m2[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mmeans [0m[1;36m2[0m[39m bytes per sample[0m[1;39m)[0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Copy the color index value to this buffer in the correct format[0m                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Pass this buffer to `cmsDoTransform`[0m                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. **Implementation approach**:[0m                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Before the loop at line [0m[1;36m1102[0m[39m, declare a properly sized buffer:[0m                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```c[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     cmsUInt16Number colorIndex;  [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m [0m[1;36m2[0m[39m bytes for TYPE_NAMED_COLOR_INDEX[0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Inside the loop at line [0m[1;36m1103[0m[39m, before calling `cmsDoTransform`:[0m                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```c[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     colorIndex = [0m[1;39m([0m[39mcmsUInt16Number[0m[1;39m)[0m[39mi;  [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m Convert the index to [0m[1;36m2[0m[39m-byte format[0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     [0m[1;35mcmsDoTransform[0m[1;39m([0m[39mxform, &colorIndex, nc2->List[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mi[0m[1;39m][0m[39m.DeviceColorant, [0m[1;36m1[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - This ensures the input buffer has exactly [0m[1;36m2[0m[39m bytes available, matching [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mTYPE_NAMED_COLOR_INDEX specification[0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. **Rationale for this approach**:[0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - TYPE_NAMED_COLOR_INDEX expects a [0m[1;36m2[0m[39m-byte color index value [0m                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m([0m[1;35mCHANNELS_SH[0m[1;39m([0m[1;36m1[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m|[0m[1;35mBYTES_SH[0m[1;39m([0m[1;36m2[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Using a `cmsUInt16Number` [0m[1;39m([0m[1;36m2[0m[39m bytes[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m instead of `cmsUInt32Number` [0m[1;39m([0m[1;36m4[0m[39m bytes[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mprovides the exact size needed[0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The formatters will read up to [0m[1;36m2[0m[39m bytes, which is now safe[0m                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - This preserves the existing transform logic and formatter selection mechanism[0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - No changes needed to formatter tables or selection logic[0m                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The fix is localized to the problematic call site[0m                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Why This Fix Works[0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. **Addresses the immediate overflow**: By providing a [0m[1;36m2[0m[39m-byte buffer, any [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mformatter reading up to [0m[1;36m2[0m[39m bytes [0m[1;39m([0m[39mor slightly beyond due to format flags[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m will stay [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mwithin safe bounds[0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   [0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. **Maintains compatibility**: The color index value is still passed correctly, [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mjust in the proper format size[0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. **No broader impact**: This fix is isolated to `CreateNamedColorDevicelink` and [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mdoesn't affect:[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Formatter selection logic[0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Other transform operations  [0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Test suites or existing functionality[0m                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The fuzzing harness code[0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. **Handles format flag variations**: Even if Extra channels or other flags cause [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39madditional reads, a [0m[1;36m2[0m[39m-byte buffer is the minimum safe size for [0m                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mTYPE_NAMED_COLOR_INDEX, and the actual formatter behavior will be bounded by this[0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Alternative Considerations[0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mAn alternative would be to validate the InputFormat in `cmsDoTransform` to ensure [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthe input buffer size is sufficient, but this would require:[0m                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Calculating expected buffer size from the format[0m                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Adding buffer size parameters throughout the API[0m                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- This would be more invasive and affect the broader codebase[0m                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe proposed fix is minimal, surgical, and directly addresses the root cause at the[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcall site where the mismatch occurs.[0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Potential Side Effects[0m                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- [0m[3;35mNone[0m[39m expected: The change maintains the same semantic behavior [0m[1;39m([0m[39mpassing a color [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mindex to the transform[0m[1;39m)[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The [0m[1;36m2[0m[39m-byte buffer correctly represents the data size expected by [0m                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mTYPE_NAMED_COLOR_INDEX[0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- All existing tests should pass as the functional behavior is preserved[0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mfix_strategy[0m[1m>[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ===Evaluation [33mEnd[0m===                                                                [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mTo understand the root cause of this issue, the following areas should be examined:[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. **`UnrollChunkyBytes` function in `src/cmspack.c` at line [0m[1;36m130[0m[39m**: This is where [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthe actual out-of-bounds read occurs. The function's implementation and how it [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39minterprets the input buffer size needs examination.[0m                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthis function, particularly regarding the expected format and size of the input [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mbuffer parameter [0m[1;39m([0m[39msecond argument[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, needs investigation.[0m                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. **`CachedXFORM` function in `src/cmsxform.c` at line [0m[1;36m537[0m[39m**: This function calls [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`UnrollChunkyBytes` and may be responsible for calculating buffer sizes or stride [0m  [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. **Color format specifications**: The transformation being performed appears to [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39minvolve reading color data. The expected input format [0m[1;39m([0m[39mnumber of bytes per [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mpixel/sample[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m versus what's being provided needs verification.[0m                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m5[0m[39m. **The `CreateNamedColorDevicelink` function context**: Understanding what color [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mspace transformations are being set up and what input format `cmsDoTransform` [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mexpects for named color conversions.[0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m6[0m[39m. **The loop variable type and transform input expectations**: The original code [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39muses an `int` loop counter while the patch uses `cmsUInt16Number`. The actual [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mexpected input type for the transform needs clarification, as both produce [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39moverflows but at different offsets [0m[1;39m([0m[39msuggesting the function is reading more bytes [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthan provided[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Fix Strategy[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<fix_strategy>[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Analysis Summary[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mAfter thoroughly analyzing the code snippets and error traces, I've identified the [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mroot cause of the stack-buffer-overflow:[0m                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Root Cause[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe issue occurs in `CreateNamedColorDevicelink` function in `src/cmsvirt.c`. The [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcode attempts to change the transform's buffer format using [0m                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`cmsChangeBuffersFormat` at line [0m[1;36m1097[0m[39m, but:[0m                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. **The return value is not checked** - `cmsChangeBuffersFormat` can fail and [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mreturn FALSE[0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. **When it fails, the old formatter remains active** - The transform retains its [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39moriginal InputFormat and FromInput formatter[0m                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. **The transform was likely created without the `cmsFLAGS_CAN_CHANGE_FORMATTER` [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mflag** - This causes `cmsChangeBuffersFormat` to fail at line [0m[1;36m1450[0m[39m of [0m              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`src/cmsxform.c`[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. **Buffer size mismatch** - The code calculates buffer stride based on the new [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mformat [0m[1;39m([0m[39mTYPE_NAMED_COLOR_INDEX = [0m[1;36m2[0m[39m bytes[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, but the old formatter [0m[1;39m([0m[39mUnrollChunkyBytes[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfor [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m-byte data[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m is still being used[0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m5[0m[39m. **Reading beyond buffer bounds** - When UnrollChunkyBytes tries to read from the[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39minput buffer, it reads beyond the allocated space of the variable `i` or [0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`colorIndex`[0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Why the Patch Failed[0m                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe previous patch changed `&i` [0m[1;39m([0m[1;36m4[0m[39m bytes[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m to `&colorIndex` [0m[1;39m([0m[1;36m2[0m[39m bytes[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, which reduced[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthe buffer size from [0m[1;36m4[0m[39m bytes to [0m[1;36m2[0m[39m bytes. However, this didn't fix the underlying [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39missue because:[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The wrong formatter [0m[1;39m([0m[39mUnrollChunkyBytes[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m is still being used[0m                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- UnrollChunkyBytes expects [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m-byte input data but the format specifies [0m[1;36m2[0m[39m bytes[0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The buffer size calculation in `cmsDoTransform` uses the format's byte size [0m[1;39m([0m[1;36m2[0m[39m [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mbytes[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, creating a mismatch[0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Fix Strategy[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe fix must be applied to `src/cmsvirt.c` in the `CreateNamedColorDevicelink` [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfunction. The strategy involves:[0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Step [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m: Check the return value of `cmsChangeBuffersFormat`[0m                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mModify lines [0m[1;36m1097[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m1099[0m[39m to check if the format change succeeded:[0m                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```c[0m                                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m Make sure we have proper formatters[0m                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mif [0m[1;39m([0m[39m![0m[1;35mcmsChangeBuffersFormat[0m[1;39m([0m[39mxform, TYPE_NAMED_COLOR_INDEX,[0m                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    [0m[1;35mFLOAT_SH[0m[1;39m([0m[1;36m0[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m | [0m[1;35mCOLORSPACE_SH[0m[1;39m([0m[1;35m_cmsLCMScolorSpace[0m[1;39m([0m[39mv ->ExitColorSpace[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    | [0m[1;35mBYTES_SH[0m[1;39m([0m[1;36m2[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m | [0m[1;35mCHANNELS_SH[0m[1;39m([0m[1;35mcmsChannelsOfColorSpace[0m[1;39m([0m[39mv ->ExitColorSpace[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    goto Error;  [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m Format change failed, abort[0m                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m}[0m                                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThis prevents using mismatched formatters when the format change fails.[0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Step [0m[1;36m2[0m[39m: Ensure proper input buffer size and type[0m                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mKeep the `colorIndex` variable from the previous patch but ensure it's properly [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39maligned and sized:[0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```c[0m                                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m Apply the transform to colorants.[0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfor [0m[1;39m([0m[33mi[0m[39m=[0m[1;36m0[0m[39m; i < nColors; i++[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    cmsUInt16Number colorIndex = [0m[1;39m([0m[39mcmsUInt16Number[0m[1;39m)[0m[39mi;[0m                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    [0m[1;35mcmsDoTransform[0m[1;39m([0m[39mxform, &colorIndex, nc2 ->List[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mi[0m[1;39m][0m[39m.DeviceColorant, [0m[1;36m1[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m}[0m                                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe `colorIndex` variable is correctly sized [0m[1;39m([0m[1;36m2[0m[39m bytes[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m for TYPE_NAMED_COLOR_INDEX [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mformat.[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Combined Fix[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe complete fix modifies `src/cmsvirt.c` around lines [0m[1;36m1096[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m1104[0m[39m:[0m                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. Add return value check for `cmsChangeBuffersFormat` and handle failure by [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mjumping to Error label[0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. Keep the `colorIndex` variable from the previous patch to provide a properly [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msized [0m[1;36m2[0m[39m-byte buffer[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThis addresses both issues:[0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Prevents execution with mismatched formatters[0m                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Provides correctly sized input buffer when format change succeeds[0m                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Justification[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Why this is optimal:[0m                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. **Minimal code changes** - Only affects the problematic function without [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mtouching formatter selection logic or other parts of the codebase[0m                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. **Defensive programming** - Checks return values and fails gracefully instead of[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcontinuing with invalid state[0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. **Preserves existing logic** - The format change is still attempted, but failure[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mis now handled properly[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. **Type safety** - Uses the correct `cmsUInt16Number` type [0m[1;39m([0m[1;36m2[0m[39m bytes[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m that matches[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mTYPE_NAMED_COLOR_INDEX specification[0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### How it preserves existing logic:[0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The same formatters and transform logic are used when successful[0m                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Error handling follows the existing pattern [0m[1;39m([0m[39mgoto Error label[0m[1;39m)[0m                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The output behavior is unchanged when format change succeeds[0m                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Only adds failure detection where it was missing[0m                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### How it addresses the issues:[0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- **Initial issue**: Prevented by checking if format change succeeded before using [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mpotentially mismatched formatter[0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- **Post-patch issue**: The [0m[1;36m2[0m[39m-byte `colorIndex` buffer matches [0m                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mTYPE_NAMED_COLOR_INDEX [0m[1;39m([0m[1;35mBYTES_SH[0m[1;39m([0m[1;36m2[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m format requirement[0m                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- **Stack overflow**: Eliminated because either the correct formatter is used with [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcorrect buffer size, or the function fails early[0m                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Potential side effects:[0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. **New failure mode** - The function may now fail and return NULL where it [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mpreviously crashed. This is safer and allows calling code to handle the error.[0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. **Debugging** - The `cmsSignalError` inside `cmsChangeBuffersFormat` will [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mprovide an error message explaining why the format change failed.[0m                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. **Transform creation requirements** - This may expose issues with how transforms[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mare created [0m[1;39m([0m[39mmissing `cmsFLAGS_CAN_CHANGE_FORMATTER` flag[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, which should be fixed [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39min the transform creation code separately if needed.[0m                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Similar solutions in codebase:[0m                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mLooking at the error handling pattern in `CreateNamedColorDevicelink`, the code [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39malready uses the pattern of checking return values and jumping to Error label [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m([0m[39mlines [0m[1;36m1075[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m1091[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m. This fix follows the same established pattern.[0m                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mfix_strategy[0m[1m>[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ===Evaluation [33mEnd[0m===                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m[01/05/26 16:19:40][0m[2;36m [0m[34mINFO    [0m Prism Supervisor Routing: TeamStatus.EVALUATE -> TeamStatus.ANALYZE                  ]8;id=615722;file:///home/qqor/crete/packages/crete/framework/agent/services/prism/__init__.py\[2m__init__.py[0m]8;;\[2m:[0m]8;id=45794;file:///home/qqor/crete/packages/crete/framework/agent/services/prism/__init__.py#160\[2m160[0m]8;;\
